Many of the questions you ask in the beginning of the survey are far too open to interpretation. For example: you do not specify about how equality should be promoted. There is a big difference between believing group equality should be sought after by changing a culture through peaceful ways, such as by education, or by the use of force, as in the use of law.

I think the one person winning at the expense of another idea is a feature of capitalism, so that's the way it is, but not the way it has to be. Stating that I believe these things to be true just means that it is a function of our current system, not that I think they are inherently or necessarily true.

I'm sure you're aware of the qualifications and limitations behind the "stances" and "beliefs" statements, but that doesn't make them less frustrating. I had to put "slightly agree" or "slightly disagree" more than I otherwise would have because the answers are more complicated and nuanced than a simple statement and simple answers would permit.
